Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray 11x7-inch baking dish. In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, and salt; set aside. In a large bowl, beat sugar and 1/4 cup butter until light and fluffy. Add egg and lemon peel; beat well. Beat in milk, then dry ingredients, just until blended. Spread 1/2 mixture in pan. Sprinkle blueberries over all. Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls over berries. In medium bowl, combine topping ingredients. Sprinkle over batter. Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until cake is deep golden brown. Cool 10 minutes before serving.